window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>'I think you know who killed your stepfather'</i>, said Wexford. So begins this scintillating collection of long and short stories by Ruth Rendell. It was clear both to Wexford and Burden that Tom Peterlee was not killed for 360 pounds, but various people would have liked them to think he was...</p><p>It is a case which reminds the Chief Inspector that there is only a thin line dividing the cop from the criminal.</p>"; 
